title: Funkadelic - Maggot Brain (1971) WAV
description:
Psychedelic Rock | 1971 | WAV 44,1 kHz Stereo 16 bit | 10mn 18s | 104 MB

Writer: Eddie Hazel, George Clinton

'Maggot Brain' is a song by the band Funkadelic. It appears as the lead
track on their 1971 album of the same name.

The original recording of the song, over ten minutes long, features little
more than a spoken introduction and a much-praised extended guitar solo by
Eddie Hazel. Music critic Greg Tate described the song as Funkadelic's A
Love Supreme; the song is #60 on the Rolling Stone list of 100 Greatest
Guitar Songs.

"Mother Earth is pregnant for the third time, for y'all have knocked her
up. I have tasted the maggots in the mind of the universe - I was not
offended, for I knew I had to rise above it all, or drown in my own shit."

The song comes along as a carefully 'refreshed' wave file, using Steinberg
Wavelab, Adobe Audition and Audacity.
